<paragraph blockId="17.[192,1440,380,696]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,380,404]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Definition.</emphasis>
A sister genus to 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, [1896]" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" box="[568,1058,380,405]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Gorgythion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[568,705,380,404]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Gorgythion</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, [1896]
</taxonomicName>
. Formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, 1899" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Chiomara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1317,1440,380,404]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Chiomara</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, 1899
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[528,582,413,437]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Moschler, 1879" authorityName="Moschler" authorityYear="1879" box="[684,1109,413,437]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Achlyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mithrax">
<emphasis box="[684,912,413,437]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Achlyodes mithrax</emphasis>
Möschler, 1879
</taxonomicName>
), but are not monophyletic with the 
<typeStatus box="[300,353,446,470]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
species (
<figureCitation box="[461,529,446,470]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="16.[192,275,1178,1200]" captionTargetBox="[192,1438,214,1144]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[192,1440,213,1144]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 6. Genomic trees of Erynnini. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677247" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677247/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Keys to F.13.1a or F. 
<quantity box="[799,885,446,470]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4036" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="in" value="13.4">13.4 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[891,1054,446,470]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans (1953)</bibRefCitation>
. Morphologically, characterized by asymmetry in male and female genitalia and distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[1106,1216,478,502]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Erynnini">Erynnini</taxonomicName>
general by a likely synapomorphy: corpus bursae in female genitalia with an additional sack-like compartment stemming from its distal end, separated from the corpus by a narrow neck and folded inside the abdomen to point caudad. In wing patterns, distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1899" box="[751,874,575,599]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Chiomara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[751,874,575,599]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Chiomara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cong &amp; Zhang &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin, 2019" authorityName="Cong &amp; Zhang &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin" authorityYear="2019" box="[934,1024,575,599]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Crenda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[934,1024,575,599]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Crenda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1032,1113,576,600]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by a discal dark bar in the cell of dorsal forewing, also present in its sister 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" box="[761,898,607,631]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Gorgythion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[761,898,607,631]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Gorgythion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly1264.13.9:G91T, aly595.7.8:A121C, aly525.18.1:T1397A, aly536.219.9:C2312G, aly260.4.1:G877C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[192,1440,721,778]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,721,745]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a masculine noun in the nominative singular, a fusion of 
<emphasis box="[1210,1267,721,745]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Chio</emphasis>
[mara], where these species were formerly placed, and [Gorgy] 
<emphasis box="[775,839,753,777]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">thion</emphasis>
, near where they ended up.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[192,1440,801,858]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,430,801,825]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[489,542,802,826]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stoll, [1780]" authorityName="Stoll" authorityYear="1780" box="[648,986,801,826]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asychis">
<emphasis box="[648,831,801,825]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Papilio asychis</emphasis>
Stoll, [1780]
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Plotz, 1884" authorityName="Plotz" authorityYear="1884" box="[997,1383,801,826]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Achlyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basigutta">
<emphasis box="[997,1240,801,825]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Achlyodes basigutta</emphasis>
Plötz, 1884
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Riley, 1934" authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1934" box="[192,552,834,858]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Chiomara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khalili">
<emphasis box="[192,404,834,858]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Chiomara khalili</emphasis>
Riley, 1934
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[192,965,883,907]" box="[192,965,883,907]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,883,907]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe Erynnina Brues and Carpenter, 1932.
</paragraph>
